==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gorgerin
<hw>Gor`ge*rin"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>gorge</ets> neck.]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>In some columns,
that part of the capital between the termination of the shaft and the
annulet of the echinus, or the space between two neck moldings; --
called also <altname>neck of the capital</altname>, and
<altname>hypotrachelium</altname>. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Column</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gorget</ent>⟦br⟧
